{"ts":"2026-06-26T01:09:48.227Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining the UI Styles**\n\nOkay, I've got a handle on the existing styles for GFF AI: dark theme, subtle neon with the specific red and blue, and a general impression of premium and expense. My next focus is the `/platforms` and `/platforms/garage` pages to evaluate where these styles are already implemented and how well they're expressed.\n\n\n**Revising `/platforms` Design**\n\nI'm now diving into the specific requirements for the `/platforms` page upgrade. The old `/platforms` had a straightforward list layout, but I need to integrate a hero section, platform grid, the Foundry Factory Garage product stack (all three!), industry mesh integrations, a control/governance layer, and a clear call to action. I'm deciding if I should rework the existing layout, or go for a much more extensive overhaul to meet all the criteria.\n\n\n**Mapping the Architecture**\n\nOkay, I'm now clarifying the scope. I realize I need to upgrade `/platforms`, `/platforms/garage`, `/platforms/foundry`, and `/platforms/factory` into premium product pages while avoiding the landing page. I've also verified the existing files and am now making a plan to create or edit `app/platforms/garage/page.tsx`, `app/platforms/page.tsx`, and `app/platforms/foundry/page.tsx`.\n\n\n**Defining the Core Pages**\n\nI'm now focusing on the `/platforms` hub page. I've confirmed that `/platforms/marketplace` doesn't require an upgrade, though I'll consider how to link it gracefully. I'm now drafting the design, which will include a hero section, platform grid (linking to `/platforms/garage`, `/platforms/foundry`, and `/platforms/factory`), and other key sections.\n\n\n**Detailing the `/platforms/garage`**\n\nI'm now detailing the `/platforms/garage` page requirements. It needs to include \"Discover AI,\" \"Workshops,\" \"AI Labs,\" and \"Experiment Zone,\" each with specific features: strategic discovery, immersive workshops, a dedicated sandbox, and a place to describe the innovation layer. I'm focusing on how these components contribute to the innovation aspect.\n\n\n**Elaborating `/platforms/foundry`**\n\nI'm currently detailing the `/platforms/foundry` page. It needs to showcase \"Build Agents,\" \"Runtime,\" \"Data Fabric,\" \"AI Engineering,\" and describe a \"co-creation layer.\" I'm planning to keep and expand on the existing interactive flow testing DAG viz for \"Build Agents,\" and detailing the other components, including a relational database ingest, agent unit testing, and how GFF AI co-creates secure products.\n\n\n"}}
